Interface QueueInterface<T>

Type Parameters:
T - data type
All Known Implementing Classes:
NotationQueue
public interface QueueInterface<T>
Interface for a Queue data structure
Author:
Professor Kartchner

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    T dequeue()
    Deletes and returns the element at the front of the Queue
    boolean enqueue​(T e)
    Adds an element to the end of the Queue
    void fill​(java.util.ArrayList<T> list)
    Fills the Queue with the elements of the ArrayList, First element in the ArrayList is the first element in the Queue YOU MUST MAKE A COPY OF LIST AND ADD THOSE ELEMENTS TO THE QUEUE, if you use the list reference within your Queue, you will be allowing direct access to the data of your Queue causing a possible security breech.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Determines if Queue is empty
    boolean isFull()
    Determines of the Queue is empty
    int size()
    Number of elements in the Queue
    java.lang.String toString()
    Returns the string representation of the elements in the Queue, the beginning of the string is the front of the queue
    java.lang.String toString​(java.lang.String delimiter)
    Returns the string representation of the elements in the Queue, the beginning of the string is the front of the queue Place the delimiter between all elements of the Queue
